Figure 4c shows the excitation fluence dependence of rubrene triplet decay in the PHJ film. The triplet decay is independent of the excitation fluence at later times (approximately > 10 μs), indicating the absence of TTA. The intrinsic triplet lifetime τT was determined to be 23 μs by fitting the later time decay with an exponential function, which is in good agreement with that obtained in a previous study50. In contrast, triplets decay faster with increasing excitation fluence at early times, indicating the contribution of TTA. Therefore, we analyzed the decay curves with a rate equation including TTA (Eq. (2))51–54.2nTt=n0exp−kTt1+n0γkT1−exp−kTt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
